Class HelperLinkedList<E>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
java.util.AbstractList<E>
aka.src.HelperLinkedList<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements held in this linked list
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>
public class HelperLinkedList<E>
extends java.util.AbstractList<E>
implements java.util.List<E>
Linked list implementation of the List interface with lazy deletion strategy. Implements all optional list operations. In lazy deletion strategy, the nodes containing removed elements are moved to a separate Linked List for future use. When a new element is added, a node is obtained from this second list if one available. A new node should be created, otherwise.
See Also:
List, AbstractList
